  "translations": {
    "en": {
      "iaql_inst": "The following statements are about how asthma affects the quality of your life. For each statement, please mark the one box below that comes closest to the way asthma has affected your life.",
      "iaql_head_a": "In the past 4 weeks, <b>because of my asthma</b>…",
      "iaql_head_b": "In the past 4 weeks…",
      "iaql_r0": "Not at all",
      "iaql_r1": "A little bit",
      "iaql_r2": "Somewhat",
      "iaql_r3": "Quite a bit",
      "iaql_r4": "Very much",
      "iaql_f0": "Never",
      "iaql_f1": "Almost Never",
      "iaql_f2": "Sometimes",
      "iaql_f3": "Often",
      "iaql_f4": "Almost Always",
      "iaql1": "I felt generally limited.",
      "iaql2": "I felt bothered by limitations in what I could do.",
      "iaql3": "I had to do things for shorter amounts of time than I would have liked.",
      "iaql4": "I was unable to do all the things I wanted to do.",
      "iaql5": "I felt frustrated that I have to do things differently than people who don't have asthma.",
      "iaql6": "It was hard to do the things I enjoy doing.",
      "iaql7": "I worried that I would have an asthma attack while visiting a new place.",
      "iaql8": "It bothered me that I always have to be aware of possible asthma triggers.",
      "iaql9": "I was kept from doing things I needed to do at work, school, or home.",
      "iaql10": "I was bothered at work, school, or home.",
      "iaql11": "I cut back on things I enjoy.",
      "iaql12": "I had to be careful what I did.",
      "iaql13": "I was afraid to be physically active.",
      "iaql14": "Everyday activities were a struggle.",
      "iaql15": "I felt bothered by having to avoid situations or places.",
      "iaql16": "I had to do a lot of planning to make sure I always had an inhaler ready.",
      "iaql17": "It bothered me that I have to plan ahead.",
      "iaql18": "I felt different than other people.",
      "iaql19": "It bothered me that I cannot do something without first thinking about how it might affect my asthma.",
      "iaql20": "Asthma placed stress on my relationships with family, friends, significant others, or co-workers.",
      "iaql21": "Asthma interfered with my romantic relationships.",
      "iaql22": "I enjoyed the time I spent with others less because of my asthma.",
      "iaql23": "It was hard having to speak up when others did things that could trigger my asthma.",
      "iaql24": "I felt frustrated that other people didn't understand my asthma.",
      "iaql25": "I felt like I missed out on doing things with others because of my asthma.",
      "iaql26": "I found myself making excuses to others because of my asthma.",
      "iaql27": "I avoided situations where my asthma might embarrass me.",
      "iaql28": "It bothered me that people thought my asthma symptoms were cold symptoms.",
      "iaql29": "I felt scared when an asthma attack came on.",
      "iaql30": "I felt frustrated that I can't fix or get away from my asthma.",
      "iaql31": "I worried about taking daily medications for my asthma.",
      "iaql32": "It bothered me that I don't know when my asthma will get worse.",
      "iaql33": "I had to worry about asthma triggers.",
      "iaql34": "My asthma was on my mind.",
      "iaql35": "I felt that asthma was controlling my life.",
      "iaql36": "I worried about becoming immune to my asthma medication over time.",
      "iaql37": "I had to make compromises because of the cost of treating my asthma.",
      "iaql38": "I struggled with the pros and cons of taking asthma medication.",
      "iaql39": "I felt like I couldn't enjoy life because of my asthma.",
      "iaql40": "I felt that asthma is preventing me from achieving what I want in life.",
      "iaql41": "It bothered me that I can't visit friends or family because of asthma triggers in their home.",
      "iaql42": "Asthma interfered with my social life.",
      "iaql43": "My asthma bothered people I care about.",
      "iaql44": "Having to avoid asthma triggers created some problems in my relationships with family, friends, significant others, or coworkers.",
      "iaql45": "I worried about having an asthma attack in front of others.",
      "iaql46": "I worried about dying from an asthma attack.",
      "iaql47": "I worried about the long-term effects of asthma on my health.",
      "iaql48": "Asthma affected my life more than I want to admit.",
      "iaql49": "I felt frustrated that I couldn't make plans in advance because of my asthma.",
      "iaql50": "I felt that I could not control my asthma.",
      "iaql51": "Managing my asthma took a lot of effort.",
      "iaql52": "I felt frustrated that I can't control the things around me that trigger my asthma.",
      "iaql53": "I worried about getting a cold with my asthma.",
      "iaql54": "I worried about not having my inhaler when I need it.",
      "iaql55": "I found it annoying having to carry my inhaler with me.",
      "iaql56": "I worried about using too much asthma medication.",
      "iaql57": "I felt dependent on my asthma medication.",
      "iaql58": "It was annoying having to make sure I had enough asthma medication on hand.",
      "iaql59": "I worried that asthma medications will make my health worse in the future.",
      "iaql60": "I was bothered by the way my asthma medication made me feel.",
      "iaql61": "It was hard to get a good night's sleep because of my asthma.",
      "iaql62": "My asthma kept me from having things I wanted to have (e.g., pets, carpet, perfume, etc.).",
      "iaql63": "I felt anxious.",
      "iaql64": "I felt irritable.",
      "iaql65": "I felt helpless.",
      "debrief": "Thank you for completing this questionnaire."
    }
  }
}